{"lemma":"شِبْرَيْ","slug":"شِبْرَيْ","root":"ش.ب.ر","root_slug":"ش-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21567","","n21571","n21572","n21573"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"span (the measure of the hand)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mete with the span, to apportion by the شِبْر (šibr)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَبَرَ (šabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dation, gift"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to magnify, to extol"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gesture, to sign with the hand"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cork oak (Quercus suber)","examples":[{"text":"وقال غيره يتخذ لها الخلايا من خشب الأرز ومن طين طيب الريح وتطين الخلايا من خارجها برماد وأخثاء البقر مدقوق معجون بالماء ويتخذ لها بعض الناس الخلايا من قشور الشبر وتسميه العامة «جناحا»","english":"And another author said that for beehives cedar wood and clay of good smell is taken and the beehives are daubed from the outside with ash and cow dung powdered and kneaded with water, and some people take for beehives the barks of the cork oak, generally called “wings”."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"A trade term presumably acquired by Arabic when it was employed for transactions to the north of the Peninsula in farther antiquity, from Hebrew שֶׁבֶר (šeḇer) in a vocalization more conservative than the Tiberian one, or from Ammonite or Old Aramaic, or even directly Akkadian 𒆬𒉻𒁺 (KU₃.PAD.DU /⁠šibirtu, šabartu, šebirtu, šipirtu⁠/, “break, fragment, lump of a stone or ore etc.”), derivations of Proto-Semitic *ṯabar- (“to break in twain”), the later Aramaic parallel to which also was borrowed by Arabic as تِبْر (tibr, “pure ore of gold or silver”).\n\nBorrowed from Latin sūber."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21567","headword_ar":"شَبَرَ","root":"$br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aborN","text_ar":"شَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~r","text_ar":"شبّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiyrN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He measured by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibor","text_ar":"شِبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"span"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (IAar, S, A, Msb, K) a garment, or piece of cloth, (S, K,) or a thing: (A, Msb:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iboru","text_ar":"الشِّبْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEotuhu","text_ar":"بُعْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAEu","text_ar":"البَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano laka A^ano","text_ar":"مَنْ لَكَ اَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obura AlbasiyTapa","text_ar":"تَشْبُرَ البَسِيطَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who will be guarantee for thee that thou wilt measure the earth with thy span?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov. applied to him who imposes upon himself that which he is unable to accomplish. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abara AlmaroA^apa","text_ar":"شَبَرَ المَرْاَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He compressed the woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abarahu","text_ar":"شَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S, A,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n. as above; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$brhu","text_ar":"اشبرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$obaArN","text_ar":"اـِشْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~rhu","text_ar":"شبّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiyrN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TS, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, TS, K *) wealth, or property, (ISk, S, A,) or a sword, (ISk, S,) or a coat of mail. (S, IB.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abira","text_ar":"شَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exulted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exulted greatly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excessively; and behaved insolently and unthankfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungratefully."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TS, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","IAar","K","ISk","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21571","headword_ar":"شَبْرٌ","root":"$br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measure"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the width"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the span,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment, or piece of cloth: so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo $aboru vawobika","text_ar":"كَمْ شَبْرُ ثَوْبِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How much is the measure of the width, by the span, of thy garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iborapN","text_ar":"شِبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whether short or tall: (TA:) pl. [app. of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$obaArN","text_ar":"اَشْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aTowala $aborahu","text_ar":"مَا اَطْوَلَ شَبْرَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How tall is his stature!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"age;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iborN","text_ar":"شِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TS, K.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaS~ara A@ll~`hu $aborahu","text_ar":"قَصَّرَ ا@للّٰهُ شَبْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iborahu","text_ar":"شِبْرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God shorten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God shortened, his life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TS, TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of giving:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, IAth:) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEN","text_ar":"بَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN","text_ar":"يَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are said for “generosity.” (A.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abarN","text_ar":"شَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due for marriage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for concubitus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, S, * K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahorN","text_ar":"مَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorN","text_ar":"عُقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sh, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTayotu AlaroA^apa $aborahaA","text_ar":"اَعْطَيْتُ الَرْاَةَ شَبْرَهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave the woman her due for marriage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for concubitus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hire that is given for the stallion-camel's covering of the female."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, S, Msb, K. *) The taking of this is forbidden. (T, S, Msb.) ―         -b8-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Marriage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K:) because it is accompanied by a gift. (IAth, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAraka A@ll~`hu fiY $aborikumaA","text_ar":"بَارَكَ ا@للّٰهُ فِى شَبْرِكُمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God bless your marriage"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a saying mentioned in a trad. (IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","A","IAth","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21572","headword_ar":"شِبْرٌ","root":"$br","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A span;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space between the extremity of the thumb and that of the little finger"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when extended apart in the usual manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) of the masc. gender: (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$obaArN","text_ar":"اَشْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the only pl. form. (Sb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buSomN","text_ar":"بُصْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSiyru Al$~ibori","text_ar":"قَصِيرُ الشِّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(applied to a man, S) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Contracted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short, in make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or, accord. to some of the lexicons,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in step."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [As a measure in astronomy, it is said in several of the law-books to be The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twelfth part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumoH","text_ar":"رُمْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and therefore"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twentytwo minutes and a half,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to modern usage: but there is reason to believe that ancient usage differed from the modern with respect to both of these measures, and was not precise nor uniform. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumoHN","text_ar":"رُمْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qibaAlu Al$~ibori","text_ar":"قِبَالُ الشِّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qibaAlu Al$~isoEi","text_ar":"قِبَالُ الشِّسْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aborN","text_ar":"شَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","A","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n21573","headword_ar":"شَبَرٌ","root":"$br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gift;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S Mgh, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aborN","text_ar":"شَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iborapN","text_ar":"شِبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the first is a word similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaTN","text_ar":"خَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaDN","text_ar":"نَفَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he who says that it is used by poetic license for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aborN","text_ar":"شَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as it is said to be in the S] is in error: ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aborN","text_ar":"شَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abarN","text_ar":"شَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are said to be two dial. vars., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadorN","text_ar":"قَدْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadarN","text_ar":"قَدَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain thing which the Christians give, one to another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataEaATaAhu Aln~aSaAraY","text_ar":"يَتَعَاطَاهُ النَّصَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"abEoDuhumo","text_ar":"َبعْضُهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaEoDK","text_ar":"لِبَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaAn","text_ar":"قُرْبَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eucharist"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking to ingratiate themselves thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eucharist"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaAn","text_ar":"قُرْبَان"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing which the Christians give"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuEoTiyhi","text_ar":"تُعْطِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one to another, as though seeking to ingratiate themselves thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh, Sgh, TA:) or (TA, in the K “and”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"powers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculties:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or (TA, in the K “and”) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gospel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","TA","IAar","K","Kh","Sgh"]}]}}